How will the code know that the stripe/file indexes are broken (i.e., written with the current writer and not the new one)?    BWT, the current  reader will read files with future version numbers; you only get a warning message:
{code:java}
      if (major > OrcFile.Version.CURRENT.getMajor() ||
          (major == OrcFile.Version.CURRENT.getMajor() &&
           minor > OrcFile.Version.CURRENT.getMinor())) {
        log.warn("ORC file " + path +
                 " was written by a future Hive version " +
                 versionString(version) +
                 ". This file may not be readable by this version of Hive.");
      }
{code}
